benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC18) cover successful resume requests with various combinations of headers and query parameters.
Non-Existing Resource: TC05 covers the case when the bundle does not exist, returning 404.
Invalid Input Validation: TC06 (invalid bundleId format), TC19 (invalid pluginProperty format), TC20 (requestedDate in the past) test input validation and error responses.
Authorization: TC07 (missing required header), TC10 (invalid user) test unauthorized access scenarios.
Concurrency Issues: TC21 tests concurrent resume requests and proper handling of race conditions.
Server Error Handling: TC14 simulates dependency service failure resulting in 500 error.
Security: TC16 and TC17 test for SQL injection and XSS attack vectors.

Edge Cases: TC11 (extra parameters), TC12 (max length headers), TC13 (large number of pluginProperty values), TC15 (retry after transient failure), TC22 (performance under load), TC23 (regression), TC24 (backward compatibility), TC25 (plugin service degraded), TC26 (whitespace and case variations in headers) cover robustness and edge cases.
gaps: Partial Update: No explicit test to verify that partial updates are rejected or handled correctly, although the API does not accept a request body, this is not explicitly tested.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover how the system handles multiple rapid requests beyond concurrency.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers or behavior.
Duplicate Submission: No explicit test for handling duplicate resume requests beyond concurrency.
Soft Deletes: No tests related to soft deletion behavior of bundles.
Pagination: Not applicable for this PUT endpoint, so no gap here.
recommendations: Add explicit tests to confirm that the API rejects any request body or partial update attempts, ensuring strict adherence to the PUT contract.
Include rate limiting tests to verify system behavior under rapid repeated requests beyond concurrency.
Add tests to verify presence or absence of caching headers to confirm caching behavior.
Add tests to explicitly verify handling of duplicate resume requests beyond concurrency scenarios.
Consider adding tests related to soft delete behavior if applicable to bundles in the system.
